    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p> </p>\n<p> Abhijeet just got his heart broken recently and thus he  decided to make a hard problem this time.<br> \nThe problem is stated below : <br> A tree containing <b>N</b> nodes and rooted at node <b>1</b> is given. On each node of the tree, there is a monkey having information about a graph <b>G</b>.\n<br>\n<b>G</b> is a graph containing <b>N</b> nodes.\nThe information contained on each node is an edge of the graph <b>G</b> .\n<br/>\nNow for every node <b>X</b>, consider the path from root to <b>X</b>. You have to collect the information about edges from this path and construct a new graph <b>G'</b>.\nThe constructed graph G' will be a sub-graph of graph G obviously.\n<br/>\nFor each node you need to find the number of connected component in graph <b>G'</b>.\n</p>\n<p> </p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line of input contains an integer <b>N</b> denoting the number of nodes in tree and the graph<b> G </b>. \n<br>\nThe next N-1 lines contains two space separated integers,U and V which  means there is a bidirectional edge between node U and node V in the tree.   \n<br>\nThe next N lines contains two space separated integers,U and V which is information contained by the node from 1 to N .\n<br>   \n\n</p>\n\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>\nFor each node starting from 1 to N, print the required answer for each node in a new line . \n  \n</p>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>U</b> \u2264 <b>N</b></li>\n\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>V</b> \u2264 <b>N</b></li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<p><h3><b>Subtasks</b></h3> <br> \n<pre>\n<b>Subtask #1 (20 points), Time limit : 1 sec\nN<=1000 \n<br>\nSubtask #2 (80 points), Time limit : 1 sec\nN<=100000\n</b>\n </pre>\n<p> </p>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n5\n3 2\n4 2\n4 1\n5 3\n1 1\n4 5\n1 5\n5 1\n3 3\n<b>Output:</b>\n5\n3\n3\n4\n3\n</pre>\n",
